'''Celluliis''' is an [[infection]] of the [[skin]], caused by [[bacteria]].<ref name=pubmed>{{cite web |url= http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmedhealth/PMH0001858/ |title=Cellulitis - PubMed Health |first= |last= |work=ncbi.nlm.nih.gov |year=13 May 2011 |quote=Staphylococcus and streptococcus |accessdate=7 October 2012}}</ref> Very often, the [[face]] is affected. The disease should not be confused with [[cellulite]]. Cellulitis is caused by bacteria, usually [[staphylococcus]] or [[streptococcus]], which can get through a break in the skin.<ref name=pubmed/> These breaks can be caused by a [[wound]], cracks in the skin, [[insect]] bites, or problems with the bodies [[immune system]]. The infection causes the skin to become red, hot and painful. It can also cause a [[fever]]. Treatment is usually by taking [[antibiotic]] drugs.<ref name=pubmed/>

